>course, 
>been well known, (for centuries ?), to geometrically arrive at the mean 
>proportion of a and b, or sq. root of the a x b product, along with 
>constructing sq. root lengths of whole numbers like 3, 7, 11, etc.
>based on 
>given lengths of unity, etc.
>
