>constructing the LENGTH of a "Cube" having equivalent volume to the 
>rectangular SOLID of sides a, b and c, or obviously the cube root of
>the a x 
>b x c product ?  I have "experimented" initially with constructing the
>mean 
>proportion of (1)a and (2)mean pro. of b and c, and combinations thereof, 
>but have not been able to arrive at the cube root of the abc product,
>etc. 
>for the solution.
>
>Jerry, I have a hunch that this construction CANNOT be done, as I don't 
>recall the constructions of cube root lengths of any whole numbers even 
>being addressed in solid geometry?
>
>I would also be very interested in knowing if this problem has been 
>submitted before by anyone??
